{"title_page": "2019 Israel State Cup Final", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football match\n|      title = 2019 Israel State Cup Final\n| image      = SammyOferSTD.jpg\n| image_size = 250\n|    caption = [[Sammy Ofer Stadium]] in [[Haifa]] hosted the final\n|      event = [[2018\u201319 Israel State Cup]]\n|      team1 = [[Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv F.C.|Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv]]\n| team1score =1\n|      team2 = [[Maccabi Netanya F.C.|Maccabi Netanya]]\n| team2score =1\n| details            = After [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]]<br>Bnei Yehuda won 5\u20134 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]]\n|  referee   = [[Eitan Shemeulevitch]]\n|       date = 15 May 2019\n|    stadium = [[Sammy Ofer Stadium|Sammy Ofer]]\n|       city = [[Haifa]]\n| attendance =\n|    weather =\n|   previous = [[2018 Israel State Cup Final|2018]]\n|       next = [[2020 Israel State Cup Final|2020]]\n}}\nThe '''2019 Israel State Cup Final''' decided the winner of the [[2018\u201319 Israel State Cup]], the 83th season of Israel's main football cup. It was played on  15 May 2019 at the [[Sammy Ofer Stadium]] in [[Haifa]], between [[Maccabi Netanya F.C.|Maccabi Netanya]] and [[Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv F.C.|Bnei Yehuda]].\n\n==Background==\nMaccabi Netanya had previously played 4 Israel cup Finals, had won the competition a record 1 time. Their most recent appearance in the final was in 2014, in which they lost 1\u20130 to [[Hapoel Ironi Kiryat Shmona F.C.| Ironi Kiryat Shmona]], and their most recent victory in the tournament was in 1978, beating Bnei Yehuda 2\u20131. \n\nBnei Yehuda had previously played in 7 finals, winning 3. Their most recent appearance in the final was tin 2017, in which they won  4\u20133 on penalties against [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]]. \n\nMaccabi Netanya and Bnei Yehuda had played each other one time was in 1978,  Maccabi Netanya won 2-1.\n\nThe two teams played each other three times during the 2018\u201319 Israeli Premier League season until the final. In the first instance Bnei Yehuda won 3\u20131, in the two other times the games end draw 1-1 and 0-0. \n\n==Road to the final==\n{| width=\"100%\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- valign=top bgcolor=#99ccff\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|Bnei Yehuda \n!'''Round'''\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|Maccabi Netanya\n|- valign=top bgcolor=#c1e0ff\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|[[2018\u201319 Israel State Cup]]\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|-\n|[[Agudat Sport Nordia Jerusalem|Beitar Nordia Jerusalem]]\n|3\u20131\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|Eighth round\n|[[F.C. Daburiyya]]\n|5\u20131\n|-\n|[[Hapoel Nazareth Illit F.C.|Hapoel Nazareth Illit]]\n|2\u20130\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|Round of 16\n|[[Hapoel Be'er Sheva F.C.|Hapoel Be'er Sheva]]\n|0\u20130  (4\u20132) after penalties\n|-\n|[[Hapoel Afula F.C.|Hapoel Afula]]\n|2\u20130\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|Quarter-finals first leg\n|[[Maccabi Petah Tikva F.C.|Maccabi Petah Tikva]]\n|1\u20130\n|-\n|[[Hapoel Afula F.C.|Hapoel Afula]]\n|1\u20131\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|Quarter-finals second leg\n|[[Maccabi Petah Tikva F.C.|Maccabi Petah Tikva]]\n|1\u20131\n|-\n|[[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maacbi Tel Aviv]]\n|1\u20130\n|bgcolor=#c1e0ff|Semi-finals\n|[[Hapoel Hadera F.C.|Hapoel Hadera]]\n|1\u20130\n|-\n|}\n\n===Details===\n{{Football box |id=\"Maccabi Netanya v Bnei Yehuda\"\n|date=15 May 2019\n|time=20:55 [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|team2=[[Maccabi Netanya F.C.|Maccabi Netanua]]\n|score=1\u20131\n|report=\n|team1=[[Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv F.C.|Bnei Yehuda]]\n|goals2=[[Guy Melamed (footballer, born 1992)|Melamed]] {{goal|4}}\n|goals1=[[Dor Jan|Jan]] {{goal|82}}\n|penalties2=[[Stav Finish|Finish]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Moti Barshatzki|Barshazki]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Tim Heubach|Heubach]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Nico Olsak]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Gavriel Kanichowsky|Kanichowsky]] {{penmiss}}\n|penalties1=[[Dor Jan|Jan]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Dolev Haziza|Haziza]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Sagas Tambi|Sagas]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Amit Zenati|Zenati]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Yuval Ashkenazi|Ashkenazi]] {{pengoal}}\n|penaltyscore=5\u20134\n|stadium=[[Sammy Ofer Stadium]], [[Haifa]]\n|attendance=\n|referee=[[Eitan Shemeulevitch]]\n}}\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n|pattern_b=_byehuda1819h\n| pattern_la=_byehuda1819h\n| pattern_ra=_byehuda1819h\n| pattern_sh=_byehuda1819h\n| pattern_so=\n| leftarm=FF5F00\n| body = FF5F00\n| rightarm= FFDD00\n| shorts = FFDD00\n| socks = FF5F00\n|title= Bnei Yehuda\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la=_mnetanya1819h|pattern_b=_mnetanya1819h|pattern_ra=_mnetanya1819h|\n | leftarm=FFFF00|body=FFFF00|rightarm=FFFF00|shorts=000000|socks=000000|\n |title      = Maccabi Netanya\n}}\n|}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|colspan=\"4\"|\n|-\n!width=25| !!width=25|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1'''||{{flagicon|LTU}} [[Emilijus Zubas]]\n|-\n|RB ||'''17'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Itzik Azuz]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]]) {{sub off|56}}\n|-\n|CB ||'''24'''||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Carlos Cu\u00e9llar]] {{sub off|75}}\n|-\n|CB ||'''2'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Dan Mori]]\n|-\n|CB ||'''7''' ||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Shay Konstantini]] \n|-\n|LB ||'''23'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Matan Baltaxa]]\n|-\n|CM ||'''19'''||{{flagicon|CIV}} [[Ismaila Soro]] {{sub off|29}}\n|-\n|LM ||'''6'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Yuval Ashkenazi]]\n|-\n|RW ||'''9'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Dolev Haziza]]\n|-\n|CF ||'''13'''||{{flagicon|CGO}} [[Mavis Tchibota]] {{yel|61}}\n|-\n|LF ||'''12''' ||{{flagicon|SVK}} [[Jakub Sylvestr]] {{sub off|100}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Substitutes:'''\n|-\n|GK ||'''55'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Yehonatan Shabi]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''26''' ||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Amit Bitton]] {{sub on|56}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''21'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Sagas Tambi]] {{sub on|29}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''10''' ||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Amit Zenati]] {{sub on|100}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''22'''||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Avishay Cohen]] \n|-\n|FW ||'''18''' ||{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Dor Jan]] {{sub on|75}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''8