=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-52076655|title=Scottish Secretary has Covid-19 symptoms|date=2020-03-28|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-28|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=expansion/>\n|}\n\n===Executive offices and others===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Executive power, cabinet, and public figures\n! Regional and other positions\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|AUT}} \n|[[Karl von Habsburg]], [[House of Habsburg-Lorraine|Head of the House of Habsburg-Lorraine]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|AUS}} \n|[[Peter Dutton]], [[Minister for Home Affairs (Australia)|Minister for Home Affairs]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|BRA}} \n|Bento Albuquerque, [[Ministry of Mines and Energy (Brazil)|Ministry of Mines and Energy]]<br>[[Augusto Heleno]], [[Institutional Security Office of Brazil|Secretary of Institutional Security]]\n|[[Nestor Forster]], [[List of ambassadors of Brazil to the United States|Ambassador of Brazil to the United States]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|Burkina Faso}}\n|[[Oumarou Idani]], Minister of Mines and Quarries<br>[[Stanislas Ouaro]], Minister of National Education, Literacy and Promotion of National Languages<br>[[Sim\u00e9on Sawadogo]], Minister of State, Territorial Administration, Decentralization and Social Cohesion<br>[[Alpha Barry]], [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Burkina Faso)|Minister of Foreign Affairs]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|FRA}}\n|[[Franck Riester]], [[Ministry of Culture (France)|Minister of Culture]]<br>[[Brune Poirson]], [[Ministry of Ecology|Secretary of State for the Ecological and Inclusive Transition]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|INA}} \n|[[Budi Karya Sumadi]], [[Ministry of Transportation (Indonesia)|Minister of Transportation]]\n|[[Bima Arya Sugiarto]], [[Bogor|Mayor of Bogor]]\n|-\n| {{flagcountry|IRN}}\n|[[Eshaq Jahangiri]], [[Vice President of Iran|Vice President]]<br>[[Masoumeh Ebtekar]], [[Vice Presidency for Women and Family Affairs|Vice President for Women and Family 