enneth Anthony Bishop, {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE}}, Counsellor, Foreign and Commonwealth Office.\n*[[Alan Stanley Collins]], Director General, [[British Office Taipei|British Trade and Cultural Office]], Taipei.\n*[[Charles Crawford (diplomat)|Charles Graham Crawford]], [[List of ambassadors of the United Kingdom to Bosnia and Herzegovina|HM Ambassador, Sarajevo]].\n*[[Kim Darroch|Nigel Kim Darroch]], lately Counsellor, Foreign and Commonwealth Office.\n*Joseph Brian Donnelly, lately Minister and Deputy Permanent UK Representative, [[North Atlantic Council]].\n*[[William Ehrman|William Geoffrey Ehrman]], lately [[Principal Private Secretary to the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs]].\n*Dr. Abraham Sek-Tong Lue, {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MBE}}, Member of the Executive, [[Great Britain-China Centre]].\n*Ralph Murphy, Counsellor, Foreign and Commonwealth Office.\n*[[Tom Phillips (diplomat)|Tom Richard Vaughan Phillips]], lately Counsellor, HM Embassy, Washington.\n*Douglas Scrafton, lately [[List of ambassadors of the United Kingdom to Yemen|HM Ambassador, Sana'a]].\n\n===[[Royal Victorian Order]]===\n[[File:Stervan de Koninklijke Orde van Victoria.jpg|thumb|Breast Star of the Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order]]\nThe [[Royal Victorian Order]] is a [[dynastic order of knighthood]] and a [[House Order|house order]] of [[chivalry]] recognising distinguished personal service to the reigning monarch of the [[Commonwealth realm]]s; admission remains in the personal gift of the monarch.<ref name=RVOBP>{{cite web| url=http://www.royal.gov.uk/MonarchUK/Honours/RoyalVictorianOrder.aspx| last=Royal Household| title=The Queen and the UK > Queen and Honours > Royal Victorian Order| publisher=Queen's Printer| accessdate=9 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n====Knights Commander (KCVO)====\n\n*[[Robin Janvrin|Robin Berry Janvrin]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CB|CVO}}, Deputy Private Secretary to The Queen.\n*Lieutenant Colonel [[John Parker, 6th Earl of M