tten]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|KBE|CB|AFC}}, Royal Air Force.\n\n:;Civil Division\n*[[Jacob Rothschild, 4th Baron Rothschild|Nathaniel Charles Jacob, Baron Rothschild]]. For services to the Arts and to Heritage.\n\n====Dames Commander (DBE)====\n:;Civil Division\n*[[Patricia Collarbone]], Director, London Leadership Centre. For services to Education.\n*[[Tamsyn Imison]], Head Teacher, [[Hampstead School]], Camden, London. For services to Education.\n*[[Mary Uprichard|Mary Elizabeth Uprichard]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE}}, President, [[Nursing and Midwifery Council|United Kingdom Central Council for Nursing, Midwifery and Health Visiting]]. For services to Health Care.\n\n====Knights Commander (KBE)====\n:;Military Division\n*Lieutenant General [[Roddy Cordy-Simpson|Roderick Alexander Cordy-Simpson]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CB|OBE}}, (474830), late [[13th/18th Royal Hussars]].\n\n:;Diplomatic Service and Overseas List\n*The Honourable Mr Justice [[John Fieldsend|John Charles Rowell Fieldsend]], lately President, Court of Appeal, Gibraltar.\n*[[Robert Peliza|Robert John Peliza]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE|ED}}, lately Chief Minister, Gibraltar.\n\n====Commanders (CBE)====\n:;Military Division\n*Commodore Anthony James Hunter Burbridge, Royal Navy.\n*Commodore Richard John Norman Hibbert, Royal Navy.\n*Colonel Paul Anthony Davis, {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE}}, (488416), late The Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment.\n*Colonel Timothy Edward Hall (489533), late The Royal Tank Regiment.\n*Brigadier [[Richard Holmes (military historian)|Edward Richard Holmes]], {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE|TD}}, (483098), General Staff Territorial Army.\n*Brigadier Robert John Shields (480395), late Corps of Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers.\n*Brigadier Michael Gordon Taylor, {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MBE}}, (475246), late Royal Corps of Signals.\n*Air Commodore [[Brian Burridge|Brian Kevin Burridge]], Royal Air Force.\n*Group Captain John Edgar Chan