{"title_page": "D'Udekem", "text_new": "{{lowercase}}\n{{Infobox noble house\n|surname          = d\u00b4Udekem\n|type             = noble family\n|native_name      = \n|native_name_lang = \n|other_name       = \n|coat of arms     = [[File:Wapen van de familie d'Udekem d'Acoz.svg|220px]]\n|image_size       = \n|alt              = \n|caption          = Coat of Arms\n|country          = {{flag|Belgium}}\n|estates          = Losange Castle, Couthof Castle, Raepenburg Castle.<ref>https://www.oostkamp.be/product/479/kastelen-en-herenhuizen</ref>\n \n|parent house     = \n|titles           = [[Count]], mostly [[jonkheer]]\n|styles           = \n|founded          = \n|founder          = \n|final ruler      = \n|current head     = Henri count d\u00b4Udekem d\u00b4Acoz\n|dissolution      = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n|deposition       = \n|ethnicity        = \n|cadet branches   = *d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz\n*d\u00b4Udekem Gentinnes\n*d\u00b4Udekem de Guertechin\n|notes            = \n}}\n[[File:Ch\u00e2teau de Losange 2012 40193.jpg|thumb|[[Losange Castle]], private property of the dowager Countess Patrick d\u2019Udekem d\u2019Acoz]]\nThe family '''d'Udekem''' ({{IPA-fr|dyd(\u0259)k\u025bm|lang}}) belongs to the [[nobility]] of Belgium since 1816.\n\n== History ==\nThe origin of the family Udekem dates back to the [[Late Middle Ages]], with the earliest member dated as dying in 1472. In the 18th century the [[Dominium]] of Acoz was obtained via marriage.\n\nUntil 2000, the head of the d'Udekem family held the rank of baron. After the wedding of [[Queen Mathilde of Belgium|Mathilde d'Udekem d'Acoz]] with the [[Philippe of Belgium|Duke of Brabant]], [[Albert II of Belgium|King Albert II]] extended the hereditary title of count to the three brothers Henri, Raoul and Patrick d'Udekem d'Acoz and to all their descendants.<ref>as per royal decree of 8 November 1999, see: [http://www.ejustice.just.fgov.be/mopdf/1999/11/13_1.pdf#Page85 Moniteur Belge, 13 November 1999, p.42488]</ref>\n\nMembers of the family were active in politics.\n\n== Descendants of Charles Joseph baron d'Udekem d'Acoz ==\n{{Tree list}}\nCharles Joseph Marie Ghislain baron (1921) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1885-1968), lord Mayor of Proven\n#* Henri Joseph Adelin Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz (1933), lord Mayor of [[Poperinge]], married in 2005 to jonkvrouw Marie-Madeleine Kervyn d'Oud Mooreghem (1940)\n#* Raoul Paul Adelin Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz (1935), local politician, married to jonkvrouw Fran\u00e7oise de Maere d'Aertrycke \n##{{Tree list/final branch}}Bernard Marguerite Jean Charles Marie Ghislain count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d\u00b4Acoz (1965)<ref>Etat pr\u00e9sent de la noblesse belge, 4th series, 2003 /2014 </ref> <br>married in 1998 to jonkvrouw [[Marie-Pierre Verhaegen]] (1966), historian<ref>Jean BASTIAENSEN, Prins Filip en prinses Mathilde: Twee families met geschiedenis, Leuven, Van Halewyck, 1999, {{ISBN|9789056172626}}</ref><ref>http://www.gva.be/cnt/oid316782/archief-marie-pierre-d-udekem-d-acoz-bekroond-met-prijs-geheim-leger</ref>\n#*{{Tree list/final branch}}[[Patrick d'Udekem d'Acoz|Patrick Paul Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie Ghislain count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz]] (1936-2008), local politician, married in 1971 to Countess [[Anna Maria Komorowska]] (1946)\n##{{Tree list/final branch}}[[Queen Mathilde of Belgium|Mathilde countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz]] (1973), married to [[Philippe of Belgium]] (1960)\n## Jonkvrouw Marie-Alix (1974-1997)\n## Elisabeth countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1977), married to Margrave Alfonso [[Pallavicini_family|Pallavicini]]\n## H\u00e9l\u00e8ne countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1979), married to baron Nicolas Janssen\n## Charles-Henri count (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1985)\n{{Tree list/end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Belgian noble families]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic families]]\n", "text_old": "{{lowercase}}\n{{Infobox noble house\n|surname          = d\u00b4Udekem\n|type             = noble family\n|native_name      = \n|native_name_lang = \n|other_name       = \n|coat of arms     = [[File:Wapen van de familie d'Udekem d'Acoz.svg|220px]]\n|image_size       = \n|alt              = \n|caption          = Coat of Arms\n|country          = {{flag|Belgium}}\n|estates          = Losange Castle, Couthof Castle, Raepenburg Castle.<ref>https://www.oostkamp.be/product/479/kastelen-en-herenhuizen</ref>\n \n|parent house     = \n|titles           = [[Count]], mostly [[jonkheer]]\n|styles           = \n|founded          = \n|founder          = \n|final ruler      = \n|current head     = Henri count d\u00b4Udekem d\u00b4Acoz\n|dissolution      = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n|deposition       = \n|ethnicity        = \n|cadet branches   = *d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz\n*d\u00b4Udekem Gentinnes\n*d\u00b4Udekem de Guertechin\n|notes            = \n}}\n[[File:Ch\u00e2teau de Losange 2012 40193.jpg|thumb|[[Losange Castle]], private property of the dowager Countess Patrick d\u2019Udekem d\u2019Acoz]]\nThe family '''d'Udekem''' ({{IPA-fr|dyd(\u0259)k\u025bm|lang}}) belongs to the [[nobility]] of Belgium since 1816.\n\n== History ==\nThe origin of the family Udekem dates back to the [[Late Middle Ages]], with the earliest member dated as dying in 1472. In the 18th century the [[Dominium]] of Acoz was obtained via marriage.\n\nUntil 2000, the head of the d'Udekem family held the rank of baron. After the wedding of [[Queen Mathilde of Belgium|Mathilde d'Udekem d'Acoz]] with the [[Philippe of Belgium|Duke of Brabant]], [[Albert II of Belgium|King Albert II]] extended the hereditary title of count to the three brothers Henri, Raoul and Patrick d'Udekem d'Acoz and to all their descendants.<ref>as per royal decree of 8 November 1999, see: [http://www.ejustice.just.fgov.be/mopdf/1999/11/13_1.pdf#Page85 Moniteur Belge, 13 November 1999, p.42488]</ref>\n\nMembers of the family were active in politics.\n\n== Descendants of Charles Joseph baron d'Udekem d'Acoz ==\n{{Tree list}}\nCharles Joseph Marie Ghislain baron (1921) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1885-1968), lord Mayor of Proven\n## Henri Joseph Adelin Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz (1933), lord Mayor of [[Poperinge]], married in 2005 to jonkvrouw Marie-Madeleine Kervyn d'Oud Mooreghem (1940)\n##  Raoul Paul Adelin Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz (1935), local politician, married to jonkvrouw Fran\u00e7oise de Maere d'Aertrycke \n###{{Tree list/final branch}}Bernard Marguerite Jean Charles Marie Ghislain count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d\u00b4Acoz (1965)<ref>Etat pr\u00e9sent de la noblesse belge, 4th series, 2003 /2014 </ref> <br>married in 1998 to jonkvrouw [[Marie-Pierre Verhaegen]] (1966), historian<ref>Jean BASTIAENSEN, Prins Filip en prinses Mathilde: Twee families met geschiedenis, Leuven, Van Halewyck, 1999, {{ISBN|9789056172626}}</ref><ref>http://www.gva.be/cnt/oid316782/archief-marie-pierre-d-udekem-d-acoz-bekroond-met-prijs-geheim-leger</ref>\n#### 2 sons and one daughter\n### 3 other daughters.\n##{{Tree list/final branch}}[[Patrick d'Udekem d'Acoz|Patrick Paul Fran\u00e7ois Xavier Marie Ghislain count (2000) d\u00b4Udekem d'Acoz]] (1936-2008), local politician, married in 1971 to Countess [[Anna Maria Komorowska]] (1946)\n###{{Tree list/final branch}}[[Queen Mathilde of Belgium|Mathilde countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz]] (1973), married to [[Philippe of Belgium]] (1960)\n### Jonkvrouw Marie-Alix (1974-1997)\n### Elisabeth countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1977), married to Margrave Alfonso [[Pallavicini_family|Pallavicini]]\n### H\u00e9l\u00e8ne countess (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1979), married to Nicolas Janssen, baron Janssen\n### Charles-Henri count (2000) d'Udekem d'Acoz (1985)\n{{Tree list/end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Belgian noble families]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic families]]\n", "name_user": "Paul Brussel", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%27Udekem"